+# 0155 — Global architecture canonical refresh
+
+0155 corrects the documentation direction after the architecture refresh audit.
+The canonical graph is `doc/docs/architecture/00_global.dot`; summary graphs may
+exist, but they must not replace the master graph or hide the established graph
+hierarchy.
+
+## Canonical graph policy
+
+- `doc/docs/architecture/00_global.dot` remains the global entry point.
+- Historical phase graphs under `doc/docs/architecture/runtime/` remain history.
+- Current-state clusters are added to `00_global.dot` when the real architecture
+  crosses a major boundary.
+- DOT files must compile with Graphviz before being considered valid.
+- A phase that changes code, contracts, runtime behavior, or architecture docs
+  must include a corresponding changelog.
+
+## Current P1 path exposed in 00_global.dot
+
+The current local P1 path is now visible from the global graph:
+
+```text
+artifact_input.md
+-> ArtifactIntakeContract
+-> ArtifactRouteRefs
+-> vector_embedding_request frame
+-> OpenVINO/E5 full vector JSON
+-> Qdrant projection with sql_ref payload
+-> vector_indexing_result frame
+-> SQL persistence handoff
+-> SQLContextStore persistence record
+-> DbApiSqlContextStore.upsert_record
+-> configured SQL DB path + readback
+```
+
+This path must remain aligned with the existing phase graphs:
+
+- `runtime/145_local_artifact_vector_indexing_runner.dot`
+- `runtime/146_artifact_intake_contract.dot`
+- `runtime/147_dynamic_artifact_route_refs.dot`
+- `runtime/148_sql_persistence_handoff.dot`
+- `runtime/149_sql_context_store_persistence_smoke.dot`
+- `runtime/150_sql_context_store_write_surface_audit.dot`
+- `runtime/151_sql_context_store_controlled_write.dot`
+- `runtime/152_sql_context_store_configured_db_path.dot`
+
+## Fixed DOT syntax issue
+
+`runtime/116_github_publication_review.dot` used `graph` as a node identifier.
+`graph` is a DOT keyword, so Graphviz failed on the edge from that node. 0155
+renames the node to `context_graph` and keeps the original meaning.
+
+## What 0155 does not do
+
+- It does not delete historical graphs.
+- It does not create a new runtime.
+- It does not change Scheduler behavior.
+- It does not add an OpenVINO, Qdrant, or SQL worker.
+- It does not choose a GitHub or VisPy implementation.
+
+## Next documentation work
+
+The next documentation pass should follow graph links from `00_global.dot` and
+update the real subgraphs in place:
+
+1. Runtime P1 subgraph alignment.
+2. Context graph current-state alignment.
+3. Inference graph current OpenVINO/E5 boundary alignment.
+4. Services graph SQL/Qdrant role alignment.
+5. Scheduler graph status alignment.
+6. Observability and GitHub graph marking as future/missing unless implemented.
+
+This must be done incrementally and backed by Graphviz compilation checks.
