+# 0155 — Changelog policy
+
+From 0155 onward, every development phase that adds or changes a meaningful
+surface must include a changelog file.
+
+## Required naming
+
+Use the existing style:
+
+```text
+doc/CHANGELOG_<PHASE>_<TITLE>.md
+```
+
+Examples:
+
+```text
+doc/CHANGELOG_0151_SQL_CONTEXT_STORE_CONTROLLED_WRITE.md
+doc/CHANGELOG_0152_SQL_CONTEXT_STORE_CONFIGURED_DB_PATH.md
+doc/CHANGELOG_0155_GLOBAL_ARCHITECTURE_CANONICAL_REFRESH.md
+```
+
+## Required content
+
+Each changelog should list:
+
+- changed files
+- new contracts
+- changed runtime boundaries
+- unchanged boundaries
+- validation commands
+- known limitations
+- next recommended phase
+
+## Rule
+
+If a phase touches any of these areas, it needs a changelog:
+
+- `src/`
+- `tools/`
+- `tests/`
+- `doc/docs/architecture/**/*.dot`
+- `doc/architecture/*.md`
+- `doc/code-rules/*.md`
+- `apply_patch_queue.py`
+
+Documentation-only phases also need changelogs when they update canonical
+architecture, Graphviz structure, code rules, or phase reports.
+
+## Reason
+
+The architecture has a long phase history. Changelogs are now the stable trail
+that links implementation, tests, graphs, and future work.
