+# Code rule — 0155 Global architecture canonical refresh
+
+`doc/docs/architecture/00_global.dot` is the canonical architecture entry point.
+
+Summary graphs may exist, but they must not replace the master graph. When the
+project crosses a major boundary, the current state must be reflected in the
+master graph and linked to relevant subgraphs.
+
+Future phase patches must include a changelog when they change code, contracts,
+tools, tests, DOT graphs, or architecture documents.
+
+DOT files must not use reserved Graphviz keywords as unquoted node identifiers.
+Use names such as `context_graph` instead of `graph`.
+
+0155 does not create any runtime orchestrator, SQL worker, OpenVINO adapter,
+Qdrant adapter, GitHub adapter, or VisPy observer.
